*     *     *     *     *     *
Merchant Tills
In Nordock Rogue and Bard characters may attempt to use Slight of Hand to steal a few coins from a vendor's purse. Simply click on this object and follow the conversation. However no reward comes without risk so note that there is a small chance of getting caught each time you try and as an illegal act if caught you face potential jail time from the guards. But a canny escape artist should be out in no time. Characters wishing to become more proficient at this should train in picking pockets. Success can only be met at each till once per reset and if discovered you cannot attempt on the same till again that reset.

This is a small mark on the stage used by performers to know where to stand.

Performances
*     *     *     *     *     *
Bards and Rogues can attempt to perform at any Bardic college or Tavern that has a "Performance Marker" By using these and following the conversation your character will attempt a performance for the crowd. If successful you will be rewarded with gold and experience points. If unsuccessful you will get no rewards. Your chance of success goes up based on your skill at performing and the possessions of a "Masterwork Musical Instrument".  The size of your reward is based on two things. Firstly the size of your crowd your reward will be multiplied by each additional Player in the area. Secondly, not all playhouses are equal. Those located in bigger cities like Brosna or Benzor though more difficult to please will yield more fame and riches. Also note that you must wait a short interval between performances called a "intermission" before you can attempt another performance.
